Ad Text:
Initial 6 Month contract 
Hybrid working Arrangments 
Lare Scale Digital Transformation Program


About the Role

We're seeking a skilled Data Architect (Information Domain) to lead the design and governance of data systems across academic, research, health,
and administrative areas. This strategic role supports the organisations digital transformation by aligning data architecture with institutional goals, enabling data-driven decision-making, and maximizing the value of data assets. You’ll work closely with the Chief Data Officer, IT, BI, and project teams to shape the Organisations data landscape.

Key Responsibilities


Develop and maintain enterprise data and integration architecture.
Align data strategies with digital transformation and compliance needs.
Create roadmaps, business cases, and investment proposals.
Support solution design for platforms like data lakes, warehouses, and MDM.
Lead data governance and chair the Data Design Authority.
Provide expert advice to ensure architectural consistency and standards.
Occasionally support hands-on project delivery.


About You
You’re an experienced Information Architect with a background in higher education or public sector, ideally with exposure to large-scale digital transformation. You bring deep knowledge of data architecture, governance, and emerging technologies, and can advise on innovation, compliance, and investment decisions.

Selection Criteria


Tertiary qualifications or equivalent experience in information management.
10+ years in Information Architecture or enterprise systems.
Familiarity with TOGAF, DAMA, and architectural frameworks.
Strong analytical, stakeholder management, and technical assurance skills.
Experience with Salesforce, AI systems (ML/GenAI), metadata, taxonomies, and cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP) is highly desirable.

Job Title: DevOps, Computational Science and Machine Learning - Various Positions
Ad Text:
The Role

Are you passionate about cutting-edge tech, agile teamwork, and making a real impact? Multiple exciting opportunities are now open for S&T5 roles within the Computational and Data Intensive Sciences (CDIS) Group — a powerhouse team driving digital transformation across DSTG.

At CDIS, we don’t just support research — we accelerate it. By partnering with DSTG researchers, we deliver high-performance digital science capabilities that empower computational science, data-intensive research, and software innovation. Our team thrives on solving complex problems with smart, scalable tech — and we’re looking for people who do too.

We’ve built some of DSTG’s most innovative platforms, including:

Tiddalik – our on-premises large language model ChatBot
Katapult – our robust software and machine learning development platform

We’re increasingly embedded in DSTG’s research community, shaping the future of Defence science through collaboration, creativity, and technical excellence.

If you're a self-starter who thrives in dynamic teams and wants to work on meaningful tech that matters — we want to hear from you.

Role 1 – S&T5 Senior DevOps Specialist

Shape the future of Defence software engineering.

Join a small, elite team of DevOps innovators driving modern software development across DSTG. As a Senior DevOps Specialist, you’ll be at the heart of a mission-critical capability — enabling researchers to build, deploy, and scale software using cutting-edge tools and practices.

This isn’t just support — it’s transformation. You’ll work alongside passionate technologists from diverse backgrounds, helping uplift DevSecOps maturity across DSTG. Our team leads by example, embracing modern engineering principles and continuously exploring new technologies to stay ahead of the curve.

If you’re a strategic thinker with deep technical expertise and a passion for modern DevOps, this is your chance to lead, innovate, and make a real difference.

Role 2 – S&T5 Team Leader Computational Science Partnerships

Bridge the gap between digital capability and scientific ambition.

Step into a leadership role within the Computational Partnerships Discipline, where innovation meets collaboration. As Team Leader, you’ll guide a nimble, high-performing team that partners directly with DSTG researchers to unlock the full potential of digital science.

This team is the connective tissue between standard service offerings and bespoke research needs — identifying gaps, crafting tailored solutions, and building repeatable models that scale across Defence Science and Technology Group (DSTG). It’s fast-paced, creative, and deeply rewarding work.

If you’re a systems thinker with a passion for enabling science through smart technology and strategic partnerships, this is your chance to lead a team that’s shaping the future of Defence research.

Role 3 – S&T5 Team Leader AI and Machine Learning Partnerships

Lead the charge in Defence AI innovation.

This is a leadership role within the Computational Partnerships Discipline, focused on enabling DSTG researchers and Defence clients to harness the full potential of AI and machine learning — especially in the rapidly evolving space of Large Language Models (LLMs).

As Team Leader, you’ll guide a high-performing team that delivers both short-term, high-impact partnerships and longer-term strategic AI/ML projects. You’ll work closely with researchers, technologists, and Defence stakeholders to explore smarter, faster ways to build and deploy domain-specific AI capabilities.

If you're a visionary technologist with a passion for AI, a knack for strategic thinking, and the drive to lead a team at the forefront of Defence innovation — this is your opportunity to make a lasting impact.

About our Team

The Research Technology and Operations (RTO) division is home to a multidisciplinary workforce of engineers, technicians, computer scientists, and digital specialists who deliver cutting-edge research services and technical solutions that underpin DSTG’s scientific and operational excellence.

Within RTO, the Computational and Data Intensive Sciences (CDIS) Group plays a pivotal role in enabling Defence research through advanced digital science capabilities. From DevOps and software engineering to AI/ML and computational science partnerships, our teams work across DSTG to deliver agile, scalable, and impactful solutions that keep Defence science at the forefront of innovation.

We operate in a fast-paced, collaborative environment where curiosity, creativity, and technical excellence are valued — and where your work directly contributes to national Defence outcomes

Our Ideal Candidate

We are looking for self-driven professionals with a strong foundation in computational science, software engineering, or AI/ML - and a passion for empowering others through technology. You thrive in agile teams, embrace change, and enjoy solving complex problems in partnership with researchers and technologists.

If you are ready to join a dynamic and supportive team committed to making a real impact in Defence research, we want to hear from you.

Application Closing Date: Friday 24 October 2025

For further information please review the job information pack, reference DSTG/07753/25 on www.defence.gov.au/apscareers

SENIOR AI ENGINEER - Bedrock/SageMaker Specialist

6 month contract
Leading enterprise organisation
Greenfield project
THE ROLE

Working with a leading enterprise client they are looking for a senior AI engineer to build AI predictive models to proactively find anomalies in their AWS infrastructure. This will be the first project of its kind in this organisation, giving you complete ownership of this project end to end.
 
RESPONSIBILITIES

Build, fine-tune and deploy Bedrock agents and SageMaker models
Create knowledge base pipelines for job logs, failure postmortems and lineage
Work with chatbot engineers to integrate LLM results into UI
Conduct testing and validation with real pipeline failures
Collaborate with architects and devops for deployment pipelines
YOU WILL HAVE

AI/ML Engineering experience with real-world deployment
Strong experience with Amazon Bedrock (Claude/Titan) and SageMaker
Experience in LLM based RAG, prompt engineering and embeddings
Strong experience with Python, Pandas, FastAPI and Streamlit
Experience explaining complex AI logic to non-technical stakeholders
 
This is an exciting opportunity for an experience AI Engineer to come into an organisation and help them on their AI journey. If this sounds like you, then please apply today!

Salary: Purchase additional leave, Online discount program
Ad Text:
About us:

At Lockheed Martin Australia, we believe that when people are empowered, inspired, and supported, they can achieve extraordinary things. We embrace flexibility, so our people can be their best inside and outside of work. We champion inclusion and continuous learning, ensuring all voices are heard and valued. And we thrive on collaboration, turning challenges into opportunities for growth and innovation.  As a leader in national security, our innovative and diverse programs create a more secure future for Australia across space, air, land, sea, and cyber domains. Every day is a chance to solve the world’s most complex challenges and make a profound impact. Experience it here.

About the program:

AIR6500 is the RAAF’s $3 billion program to develop a joint air battle management system that builds on the capabilities offered by Next Generation sensor and command and control systems. AIR6500 will create a fully networked ‘system of systems’ that synchronises air and missile defence operations in joint and coalition environments, maximising situational awareness and enhancing the speed of decision making across the battlespace.

Responsibilities

The Mission System ICT Lead shall:

·         Lead specific analysis and design activities to develop test and deliver the AIR6500 Mission System ICT solution

·         Guide the design, development, and testing of COTS/MOTS or custom computing hardware

·         Co-ordinate with hardware, systems and test engineers to deliver an integrated product

·         Manage the design and installation of ICT components and assemblies into chassis, racks, cabinets, workstations, customer facilities, and/or shelters

·         Development and Management of ICT Mission System Objective Evidence for sell off and acceptance

·         Guide the AIR6500 Mission System Hardware solution and interfaces in the MBSE architectural model

·         Evaluate Mission System ICT Hardware and non-functional related requirements, conduct product trades, define the sell-off approach

·         Work with IPTs and System Architects to establish ICT Mission

·         Hardware requirements and sizing for AIR6500 elements

·         Lead the development of Key AIR6500 technical documents and artefacts such as solution description, trade studies and definition of requirements

·         Work with a broad set of stakeholders, across the Lockheed

·         Martin Business and design partners for the achievement of common goals

·         Ensure AIR6500 Mission System ICT design converges to a solution which will enable the System to have an Authority to Operate and Authority to Connect to strategic networks

About you:

To be successful in this role you will also have:

·         Experience in ICT Hardware Engineering design for Critical Mission Systems.

·         Excellent understanding of the system/subsystem engineering lifecycle as it relates to Hardware Engineering using standard methods and techniques/tools.

·         Significant experience in creating engineering documentation including technical drawings

·         Knowledge of Australian Regulations and Certifications

·         Knowledge of the ISM controls and how these are incorporated into requirements and design.

·         Excellent analysis skills with an ability to develop and evaluate alternatives to determine best value based on customer-provided performance weighting

·         Proficient in concept development

·         Advanced verbal communication skills including both speaking and listening to the customer

Desirable

Any knowledge of:

·         Knowledge of packaging for ruggedized deployable land-based systems

·         Model-based System engineering experience (Rhapsody experience)

·         Requirement decomposition (DOORSNG experience)

An awareness of:

·         Infrastructure hardware technologies including computing

(servers, clients, storage) network, cross domain solutions

·         Agile Engineering Methodology

·         Configuration Management principals and experience with configuration management tools 

How we reward and support you:

When you join Lockheed Martin, you work on projects you won’t experience anywhere else.

We offer you a range of benefits built to suit you, no matter what stage of life you are in. 

·         Flexible work & Hybrid work options

·         Access to our online discounts program offering immediate discounts or cashback

·         A variety of leave options including Purchase Leave to support you and your family  

·         Additional benefits such as Novated Leasing and Fitness Programs

·         Learning & Development platforms to encourage ongoing self-development

Special Requirements:

Applicants must be eligible to obtain and maintain an Australian Defence Security Clearance and employment may be contingent on the provision of further personal information including citizenship to ensure compliance with international export control legislation and regulations.

A Veteran-friendly Workplace:

Veterans are encouraged to apply. We highly value the unique skills and experiences that veterans and transitioning service members can contribute to our team. We are proud to be recognised as a Veteran Friendly Employer by the Australian Government.
